HEADWORD: Cross-bun
<hw>Cross"-bun`</hw> <pr>(-b⟦ucr⟧n`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A bun or
cake marked with a cross of icing, and intended to be eaten on Good
Friday; also, called <altname><er>hot cross bun</er></altname>, even
when not hot.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

